   "notes": "Heavy scene from pbrt contemporary-bathroom. ref via: python tests/pbrt/regen_refs.py --scene bathroom --res 256 --spp 256 --integrator path (rendered with pbrt's PATH integrator to match skinny's path anchor; the authored sppm EXR is unclamped \u2014 max~2120, bypassing maxcomponentvalue \u2014 and pbrt's own path-vs-sppm differ by relMSE~0.63 on this caustic scene). FIREFLY CATASTROPHE FIXED (change film-maxcomponent-clamp): skinny now applies the pbrt film maxcomponentvalue=50 per-sample radiance clamp, so path|wavefront vs pbrt dropped 232.8 -> ~0.34 and bdpt-vs-path dropped 6612 -> 0.36 (MSE 0.017, structurally identical); skinny max 7985 -> 50; path megakernel==wavefront still 0.0000. STILL KNOWN-DIVERGENT for two residuals (each a separate follow-up that must LOWER these baselines): (1) pbrt-truth ~0.34 relMSE = RGB-vs-spectral / blackbody-emitter-normalization (skinny normalizes blackbody to unit-luminance, pbrt to peak-spectral-1); (2) self-consistency relMSE vs the path anchor stays large from dark-pixel /b^2 amplification on this noisy scene (BDPT MSE 0.017 but relMSE 0.36) plus a genuine sppm-vs-path estimator difference (sppm MSE 10.4, relMSE 65) \u2014 a metric-robustness follow-up. emissive-triangle-bsdf-mis (2026-06-24): path BSDF-hit MIS complement fixes area-light dim bias; bathroom mean 1.36->0.97, path FLIP 0.222->0.155 (megakernel==wavefront relMSE 0.0000). relMSE baseline 0.342 unchanged (exposure-aligned gate is brightness-blind; residual = RGB-vs-spectral). BDPT/SPPM/neural/restir baselines re-measure in their own changes (Path anchor moved brighter). SPPM BLACK-WALLS FIXED (change fix-sppm-bathroom-black-walls, 2026-07-04): sppmLoadMaterial rebuilt the deposit-time FlatMaterial without the Stage-2 rich inputs (transmissionColor/specularColor/diffuseRoughness, added to FlatHitMat by flat-lobes-rich-inputs AFTER PM-1 shipped) -> undefined values zeroed EVERY photon deposit (tau==0 scene-wide, indirect term dead, walls black). VisiblePoint now stores the three fields (scalar 152->180 B, MSL 192->240 B) and sppmLoadMaterial rebuilds them; test_sppm_state.py locks FlatHitMat-subset-of-VisiblePoint so a future FlatHitMat field cannot silently break the deposit again. measured sppm_vs_path relMSE 64.97 -> 2.59 (MSE 10.42 -> 0.297), linear-mean ratio sppm/path = 1.007 at 128 spp. measured sppm|wavefront pbrt-truth moved 0.364 -> 1.71: the OLD number was an artifact of the bug (black walls contribute 0/(ref^2) exactly where the noisy-dark /b^2 amplification lives; a lit-but-noisy wall scores worse than a black one) and the path anchor itself measures 0.83 vs its 0.342 record under the current code (anchor drift is a separate follow-up; sppm baseline left at the aspirational 0.364, scene stays known_divergent/xfail).",
